Description: Ichigo Kurosaki sees dead people and must help usher them safely into the afterlife.
Title: BLEACH,  VOL. 32
Author: Tite Kubo

Description: Alice wanders into a very different part of Wonderland in this interpretation of the classic tale. In this new area of the fantasy land, every man is in love with Alice... and firearms.
Title: ALICE IN THE COUNTRY OF HEARTS, VOL. 4
Author: Quinrose and Hoshino Soumei

Description: Isn’t being a kid hard enough? For this group, who are also part bird, nothing comes easy. An F.B.I. agent steps in to help, but the evil "erasers" lurk around the corner.
Title: MAXIMUM RIDE, VOL. 3
Author: James Patterson and NaRae Lee
Contributor: by James Patterson and NaRae Lee

Description: This series, described as a romantic comedy, is about the relationship between Misaki and Akihiko, a male tutor, who meet when Misaki needs help with college entrance exams.
Title: JUNJO ROMANTICA, VOL. 12
Author: Shungiki Nakamura

Description: The origins and true nature of Pain, Naruto’s arch nemesis, are revealed.
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 48
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: Chibi is a vampire with a twist: rather than suck blood, this young, female vampire has to expel it. This series fills in some of her back story and includes behind-the-scenes material.
Title: CHIBI VAMPIRE AIRMAIL
Author: Yuna Kagesaki

Description: Tsukune Aono’s new school is filled with vampires and werewolves. And the girl he is interested seems to have eyes for him, but is it his blood she’s after?
Title: ROSARIO + VAMPIRE: SEASON II, VOL. 2
Author: Akihisa Ikeda

Description: This series tells the story of Itsuki Minami, the toughest kid at Higashi Junior High School. In this installment, mysteries and confrontations abound.
Title: AIR GEAR 15/16/17, VOL. 15
Author: Oh!Great

Description: Misao Harada can see into a magical realm where she is the bride demon of prophecy. How will she survive the pursuit of demons who want the power in her blood?
Title: BLACK BIRD, VOL. 5
Author: Kanoko Sakurakoji

Description: This manga series is about Moritaka Mashiro, who enjoys drawing and Akito Takagi, a would-be writer, who team up to create a manga series. Will they survive the world of publishing?
Title: BAKUMAN, VOL. 1
Author: Tsugumi Ohba and Takeshi Obata
Contributor: by Tsugumi Ohba and Takeshi Obata
